                "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                "paragraphTitle": "Let's eat",
                "paragraphSubtitles": ["Around the world"],
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "How many people are there in your family? How much food do you eat in a typical week? Do you eat more packaged food or fresh food? What's your favorite food? And how much do you spend on food each week? Here, we take a look at food habits in different countries."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                "paragraphTitle": "Ecuador",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "In Ecuador, most families don't eat any packaged food at all. People usually buy fresh food in local markets and they eat a lot of fruits and vegetables, as well as rice and potatoes. People usually buy food every day to cook at home. Lunch is an important meal and most children go home for lunch in the afternoon. Families usually eat together."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                "paragraphTitle": null,
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphImage": "",
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Average cost of food per week: $30",
                  "Popular food: rice, potatoes, chicken"
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                "paragraphTitle": "The US",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphImage": "",
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Most people in the US eat a lot of packaged food. They don't eat a lot of fresh fruit and they don't eat many vegetables. Meat is very popular here, as well as dairy products, like milk and cheese. Most Americans go to a big grocery store once a week to buy food. There aren't many markets, but some towns have a farmer's market once a week. A lot of families regularly eat at restaurants or eat fast food in front of the TV or in the car."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 5,
                "paragraphTitle": null,
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphImage": "",
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Average cost of food per week: $400",
                  "Popular food: corn, chicken, hamburgers"
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 6,
                "paragraphTitle": "Italy",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphImage": "",
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Italy is famous for its food, and for most Italians, food is a very important part of their day! Markets are very popular, but most people buy their food at a grocery store. Most people buy fresh bread every day, and they use milk mainly with coffee. Italians don't eat much packaged food, but people often buy cans of tomatoes and beans. The main meal of the day is usually lunch."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 7,
                "paragraphTitle": null,
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphImage": "",
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Average cost of food per week: $200",
                  "Popular food: pasta, rice, fish, bread"
                ]
              },
